==English==
===Noun===
{{wikipedia}}
'''waterline'''

#{{nautical}} the line formed by the [[surface]] of the [[water]] on the [[hull]] of a [[ship]] when she is [[afloat]]; any of a series of short lines marked on the hull to show where the waterline would be under different [[loading]]s
# a line showing where the water has been, usually a line separating dry land and wet areas; a [[watermark]] or [[tidemark]]
# (''makeup'') the inner rim of the eyelid, just behind the [[lash line]]; primarily used in reference to the application of [[eyeliner]]
